Prevent service from looking for removed file in new revisions.

This patch prevents the service from checking if a file, which
was removed in the past, is in the newer revision. If the file
is being "re-added" with the same name in the same location then
we still perform the search to get the newest annotation.

Add stress test client and all required changes.

This patch adds a client that performs a stress test
on the service by querying for 1000 file chunks every
X seconds, at different revisions, where X is
decreasing over time. It stops when there are too
many items to process in the queue and only after
this happens more than once. tests/stress_client.py requires
that tuid/app.py and tests/sqs_consumer.py are running
for the stress test to be performed.

Fix cached response from client.py

This patch fixes the cached response retrieval and insertion
and also fixes a couple of bugs in sqs_consumer.py when there
are no requests to process.

Add daemon to TUID service with a local test, and fix some bugs.

This patch adds a daemon to the service that can be run to update
the frontier files to the latest known coverage revisions. It also
adds a test that can be ran locally to watch the daemon run. To make
the daemon possible, some other changes aalso needed to be made to
other portions of the service (like `get_tuids_from_files`).

Fix updating and insertion, diff application, and removed file queries.

This patch changes some settings in config.json to be able to properly
insert and update entries. Fix the diff application to strip starting
forward slash. Finally, make it simpler to deal with removed files.

Enable diff-based frontier updating, fix tests, and optimize

This patch replaces annotate-based frontier updating with a diff-based solution
that is achieved with a minimum number of network requests (2 requests, and the
test 'test_one_http_call_required' is changed to reflect this). The SQLite DB
updates and insertions are also optimized through this patch.
